4.2 Evaluation Methodology
4.2.1 Gold Standard Creation
Gold Standard Annotation Process
Step 1: Sample Selection
  - Select 2 10-K filings (FY2023, FY2024) for annotation
  - Extract all nodes from selected filings
  - Stratified sampling across node types

Step 2: Expert-Specific Annotation
  - Cross-Reference: Annotate 200 reference pairs (100 pos, 100 neg)
  - Causal: Annotate 200 causal relationships (100 pos, 100 neg)
  - Temporal: Annotate 200 temporal links (100 pos, 100 neg)
  - Table-Text: Annotate 200 alignments (100 pos, 100 neg)
  - Semantic: Annotate 200 similarity pairs with 1-5 score

Step 3: Inter-Annotator Agreement
  - Two annotators per expert type
  - At least one annotator with finance/accounting background
  - Required Cohen's Kappa > 0.7
  - Resolve disagreements via third annotator adjudication

